UnderAverage Decathlon standard. I'm used to better standard from the other stores.
Fantastic place provides very good quality and delicious food. Staff are very friendly and helpful.
Best service in the area! Really kind staff. Thanks for everything!
Just Loved it, very good people and very good food.

Awesome! We could only spend 2 nights but we would move in :) This place is the nice combination of old-school vintage design and comfort. Surrounded by family friendly "mountains", is a great location to get far from the big city, but still have the option for a warm shower.
This place is a must!

Was expecting more considering how many recommendations I got for this place. The lamb chops (ordered medium, they came out closer to well done) were very tough and chewy. The calamari was better, but still a little over. Good flavour in all the sides, and the date and orange sticky toffee pudding was nice. The decor and atmosphere was nice, with a good view of the place des epices. The staff were lovely, however our reservation was not confirmed by email, despite the website saying that it would be. No alcohol, contrary to what other sites online said about the place.
Wonderful spot! Great food and awesome service! Dined there two evenings on our trip because it was so delicious

Perfect place for eating at any time of the day, but dinner on their rooftop gives you an amazing memory of the city. This chic restaurant felt like a getaway from the chaotic streets, as it's not a typical marrocan restaurant. Great food, even better deserts, very friendly staff and impeccable service. Don't hesitate and make a reservation for a table there :)

Ordinarily this meal would have been a 3* after the ridiculously overpriced house salad to start. The cous cous main here however is m, hands down, the best plate of food I've ever had in a restaurant. The tenderness of the meat, balance of the spices, crispy texture of the cauliflower... I had to close my eyes when eating. Bloody fantastic. Service is cool too.

The setting is wonderful, nestled in the far North-East corner of the Souks. The restaurant was full of non natives in 2's, 3's and 4's. The menu was somewhat limited and the meals were okay on the whole without being full of the promise that the decor and ambience deserved. I would not rush back.

properties.address: ul. "Olimpijska" 4, 1756 g.k. Sofia park, Sofia, Bulgaria

reviews.text:
All sports are easily started with Decathlon. They not only have lots of goods but also a maintenance corner for bikes, ski, snowboard. Seperately you may buy there compact instruments and fix your equipment yourself. 
The shop offers print outs on T-shirts (the staff can assist or you can provide the image via flash drive). Cups and medals are also available with different text on them. 
Thumbs up for every service they have.
The best quality to price products! Usually quite full with people and in peak seasons some of the products might be sold out. Still, almost everythime the thing you are after is there.

Sells only junk at inredibly high prices. Product placement is horrible, order is nonexistent. Overcrowded. The whole store is dirty, dusty and smells of cheap plastic and cheap glue. 10 minutes in and my throat was scratchy and I wanted out.
You can find clothing and what not for almost every sport you can think of. The store is quite big too. The staff there is nice and helpful.
Chaotic and practically empty. Whole aisles of nothing. I don't understand why they don't just close a few days for the change of season.

properties.name: NoMad Bar
properties.address: 10 W 28th St, New York, NY 10001, USA

reviews.text:
Great setting! Good food. 
3 stars because it wasn't out of the world. The drink was okay! And the food was definitely delicious but super over priced! Did not seem worth it at the end of it all. 

One thing you must try is their carrot tartare: they do one hell of a job with that dish! It's amazing!

Good variety of well-made cocktails.  They even have some "large-format drinks" that looked pretty amazing.  

Warning: the prices are on the high side.  Also if you just are drinking, you generally will just be standing at tables near the bar.  But on the other hand, reservations are not needed, which is nice.
Nice & fancy alternative in mid town. The Service it's excelent 10/10. A bit pricy, the food is not such a big deal

Cool bar with a hip, trendy and young crowd. The bar is large and serves a large variety of cocktails. The standerd ones are not on the menu, but that makes it fun to try out new ones. The staff is very helpfull. Its expensive though.
Best dry aged burger in NYC (darn good everything else too).  Also it's a got a great style and ambiance to eat and drink in.  Will get VERY crowded quickly though, so try and get there early
